Lavall Hall was fatally shot by Miami Gardens police on February 15 after he 'attacked' them with a broom . 
  His family has filed a wrongful death lawsuit against the city and the two officers . 
  Footage shows shell cases flying as he runs away from police officers . 
  Police said he attacked them with 'deadly force' but family say he was running away from them . 
  Hall was diagnosed with schizophrenia and bipolar disorder . 
  He had been released from a mental hospital just one week before the shooting . 
 